<br>
TLC's only effect that I can see is to seriously inhibit questing -- especially quest discovery.  It creates a major obstacle to all quests that the quest designers don't take into account when designing quests; ie. it makes quests a lot harder, more prone to bugs, and bugs less likely to be fixed.  Due to the substantial increase in quest diffictulty, it behooves all FV questors to let other servers solve the quests and post full spoilers before we attempt them here.  Effort versus reward ratio on FV is a lot higher than on other servers.<br>
<br>
TLC needs to be removed.  OTH, TLC is not why I'd consider leaving FV.  If I moved to a different server, it would be due to the lack of multiple characters.  There's a serious bank-slot shortage here and with TLC you really *need* an army of mules to bank all the quest items you find as you level up -- you can't ever go back and get them later.  I've been out of bank slots since about level 12, most of it taken by TLC'd quest items I plan to use later.<br>
<br>
So, on FV, I don't like TLC and I don't like the character limit.  I do like the language changes.  I don't like the grouping restrictions, but I like the buffing restrictions (both alignment and level).  All of these fall into the background noise, though.<br>
<br>
The reasons I started up again on FV instead of one of the other servers was 1: it's a new server, 2: it's an &quot;RP&quot; server, 3: it's small, and 4: the people on this board sounded fun.  The new ruleset, to me, is mostly just an ad-hoc unsupported joke by Verant that I have to get around. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umalathos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malathos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/10/02 10:34:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm ,,</span><hr size=1> I think that part of the problem is that most of the people on FV have alts or even mains on other servers and are used to operating under a different set of rules. The rules on FV are different, but we (and yes, I do include myself here) are still trying to use methods that work with the old rulesets.<br>
<br>
The rules HAVE changed. We must adapt to the new ruleset and find new ways to cope with the problems it presents us with. <br>
<br>
I arrived in Qeynos too late in life to do quest for the Int earrings in the aqueducts (L17 Wiz from Freeport). So when I get the time, I plan to hire a couple of mercenaries to go and get them for me. On the other hand, I'm heading to High Pass Hold to obtain a certain Testament of Vaneer. I plan to use it in trade at a later date (assuming the no drop flag has now gone).<br>
<br>
I'm hoping that the population will slowly rise as the economy builds up and should also be given a boost when the Bazaar is finally opened for trading. This will enable newbies to stack up on TLC items they can get hold of and then put them up for sale in the Bazaar.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure how it's all going to work out, but I'm definately hanging around to find out.<br>
